Package: HetEffects
Title: Ensemble Methods for Heterogeneous Treatment Effects
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Solomon", "Messing", email = "solomon.messing@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Justin", "Grimmer", role = "aut"),
    person("Sean", "Westwood", role = "aut")
  )
Author: Solomon Messing [aut, cre], Justin Grimmer [aut], Sean Westwood [aut]
Maintainer: Solomon Messing <solomon.messing@gmail.com>
Description: Implements ensemble methods for estimating heterogeneous treatment effects,
    extending Grimmer, Messing & Westwood (2017). The package combines multiple machine
    learning methods (LASSO, elastic net, BART, random forests, causal forests, XGBoost,
    and more) using cross-validation to optimize ensemble weights. Supports both
    randomized experiments and observational studies with propensity score weighting.
    Provides analytic standard errors via influence functions and bootstrap inference.
